description:
popup.js:rerenderLog wipes log.innerHTML and rebuilds on every renderActivity. With 100 entries each carrying expandable details, the rebuild costs ~5-15ms. renderActivity fires on every command start AND every command done (2× per command). At 10 cmd/s burst, that's ~100-300ms/s in popup rebuilds — noticeable when the pop-out window is open.

Fix: coalesce calls via requestAnimationFrame:

  let renderPending = false;
  function rerenderLog() {
    if (renderPending) return;
    renderPending = true;
    requestAnimationFrame(() => {
      renderPending = false;
      actuallyRerender();
    });
  }

5 lines, no diff cost. Removes the 5-15ms cost burst from chained agent loops.

A bigger win (deferred to a separate bead if needed): diff-based update that keeps entry DOM nodes keyed by id and only updates the changed row. Removes the cost entirely but is ~50 LOC.

Start after PR #3 lands (it has — fa43969).

Found by: performance-oracle review of PR #3.
